-- Continental AG Raises Forecast, Targets 15% Sales Growth as Earnings Climb
-- Tom Lavell
-- 2010-07-02T10:05:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/continental-ag-raises-forecast-targets-15-sales-growth-as-earnings-climb.html

          
          
             Continental AG is forecasting a 15
percent increase in full-year revenue after sales jumped 38
percent in the first half.  
 Revenue in the six months through yesterday rose to 12.5
billion euros ($15.6 billion) from 9.06 billion euros, while
earnings before interest and taxes probably rose to 1.2 billion
euros from 248.8 million euros, the Hanover, Germany-based car-
parts maker said today in a statement.  
          
          


  


        